instruction: Make a list of 20 macroeconomic indicators.
output:
List of 20 Macroeconomic Indicators: 

1. Gross domestic product (GDP) 
2. Unemployment rate 
3. Inflation rate 
4. Interest rate 
5. Balance of payments 
6. National debt 
7. Money supply 
8. Consumer price index 
9. Currency exchange rate 
10. Business cycle 
11. Housing prices 
12. Government spending 
13. Tax revenue 
14. Savings rate 
15. Capital investments 
16. Manufacturing production 
17. Commodity prices 
18. Construction activity 
19. Productivity rate
